\par 
\par \pard\qc\plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b TABLE OF CONTENTS
\par \pard\li720\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx2160\tx7920\plain\lang1024\f2\fs24\cf0\b MOSAIC OA OVERVIEW\tab 3
\par \pard\li720\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx7920\plain\lang1024\f2\fs24\cf0\b WHAT'S NEW IN THIS VERSION\tab 3
\par WHAT'S COOL IN THIS VERSION\tab 4
\par \pard\li720\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx7920\plain\lang1024\f2\fs24\cf0\b What's New in IBAE\tab 4
\par Installation Notes\tab 4
\par Errata\tab \tab 4
\par Bug and Enhancement Log\tab 5
\par Free Font License Agreement\tab 29
\par 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b MOSAIC OA OVERVIEW
\par \plain\f5\fs20 This package contains the Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs20\b  \plain\f2\fs20 (MOA) Runtime & Development Environment (RDE) Release 1 Version 4.  It is for use with the Microsoft Windows NT 4.0 and the Windows 95 operating systems. Other Mosaic OA products such as the Foundation Application Package (FAP), AIMS (V1.9 required for RT R1V4), CDServer for NT, CDServer for Unix, CDS/ODBC Driver, and MOA Printer Drivers are released separately. 
\par 
\par \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f6\fs20\b  \plain\f2\fs20 provides a migration path from Pinnacle Plus Release 4/5.  The PCL code and most Data Dictionary objects may be converted via the conversion program \plain\f2\fs20\b PCL2OFB\plain\f2\fs20  (see the \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs20  RunTime System Reference Manual, ISD #00023) and used with the \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs20\b  \plain\f2\fs20  Version 4 Data Dictionary. Additionally, there is some degree of compatibility with Pinnacle Plus Release 4/5 C subroutines. No OFB code conversion is required to upgrade from \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs20\b  \plain\f2\fs20 Version 3 to \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs20\b  \plain\f2\fs20 Version 4 (For those still wanting to run FAP 1.3, see the note in the ReadMe.Moa file contained in the distribution).
\par 
\par MSVC++ version 4.2 was used to build the various EXEs and DLLs that are parts of this version of Mosaic OA.
\par 
\par The Mosaic OA stylized logo, as seen in this document, is now a true registered trademark.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b WHAT'S NEW IN THIS VERSION
\par \pard\li1080\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Mosaic OA no longer includes printer drivers. They are sold separately.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The OFB compiler now validates OFB subroutine compiled sizes and reports an error if a subroutine would exceed the maximum size of a Data Dictionary OFB object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added "SETFACE RT_TRANSPARENT" support to rendering of boxes, check boxes and radio buttons.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The Mosaic OA RunTime now assigns the Interpreter's primary window handle to the field FLD:common:RThWnd if and only if this field is present in the data dictionary. The field common:RThWnd should be defined as an INT type field, length 4
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf0 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}On normal exit, a new OFB common exit routine, \plain\f2\fs20\cf0\b common:exit_point\plain\f2\fs20  provides a convenient point to perform application cleanup, such as unloading DLL's, resetting application states and other general application exit management tasks, prior to the exit from the Mosaic OA RunTime interpreter.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}A new DDPROJ.INI Personality switch - \plain\f2\fs20\b\ul PPLUSCOMPATIBLE\plain\f2\fs20  has been developed for this version of the MOSAIC OA RunTime.  This switch is used for a variety of compatibility issues as the need arises.  Set bit 0 to\plain\f2\fs20\i  \plain\f2\fs20\b\i not\plain\f2\fs20\i  gray\plain\f2\fs20  RELIEFBUTTONS when they are disabled.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}New DDPROJ.INI Personality switch - \plain\f2\fs20\b\ul STRETCHFIELD\plain\f2\fs20 .  This switch \plain\f2\fs20\i stretches\plain\f2\fs20  the displayed field size when using proportional fonts in the DRAW FIELD and DRAW COMBOFIELD verbs.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The CSR comm_trimstring has been removed from CSR.DLL. 
\par \pard\li720\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b WHAT'S COOL IN THIS VERSION
\par \plain\f2\fs20 Mosaic OA applications may now be developed to be OLE automation servers and clients.  This provides another standard means of inter-process communication for local and remote OLE automation clients and servers.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b What's New in IBAE 
\par \pard\li1080\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}An updated look and feel. IBAE is now very similar to other made-for-Windows 95/NT applications.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Tip of the Day
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Integrated AIMS support
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}SpecPad, a new specification tool based on Microsoft's WordPad. Use the SpecPad tool in preference to 'Ddspec' which is now obsolete.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Import tools for bitmaps, icons and CSRs.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Many jumps added in IBAE author online help for accessing the Runtime System Reference online help.
\par \pard\plain\f7\fs20 
\par 
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b Installation Notes
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf2\b Note for Windows 95 setup:\plain\f2\fs20   Use uppercase letters for the workgroup name. (Lowercase is the Windows NT default.) The Mosaic OA message switch does not work if the workgroup name is set up in lower case letters.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b Errata
\par \plain\f2\fs20 This section contains notes and workarounds or corrections on bugs and/or errors that escaped our notice before cutting the distribution cd-rom. 
\par \pard\li1080\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The data dictionary specification print tool 'ddspec' prints garbled (overwritten) output when printing screens under Windows 95.  We recommend using the new 'SpecPad' tool instead of 'ddspec'.  Ddspec is now obsolete and will not be available in future releases of the IBAE toolset.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}A bug exists that prevents the help file from displaying when you press F1 from any of the subordinate dialogs in the Desktop Transaction author. To access the help topics for these subordinate dialogs (Attributes, Side Bars, Titles, Buttons/Menus, Routines, Screens) press F1 when the main Desktop Transaction dialog is displayed, then click on hotspots on the main help graphic. You can also locate these topics in the help index.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf3 
\par \plain\f5\fs28\cf1\b Bug Fix and Enhancement Log
\par \pard\li360\ri360\qc\plain\f5\fs28\b Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs28\b  Development Tools & RunTime 
\par \pard\li360\ri360\plain\f2\fs24 Listed below are all changes implemented in the \plain\f5\fs22 Mosaic OA\plain\f2\fs24  RunTime Executive, Console Tools and IBAE Authors,. 
\par \pard\li360\ri360\qc\plain\f2\fs24\b Release 1, Version\plain\f2\fs24  \plain\f2\fs24\b 4\tab P/N:\plain\f2\fs24  \plain\f2\fs24\b 85-35006-Dxx\plain\f2\fs24 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\i 
\par \pard\li360\plain\f2\fs18\b NOTE: Changes are listed in chronological order, beginning with the latest changes first. Please enter your changes without any extra spaces or formatting. You can use the styles described below If you like.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 
\par 8-27-97 R1V4.10.1 (Containing Patch 1) Complete
\par \plain\f2\fs24 
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added/replaced miscellaneous source and header files residing in <MOADIR>\\SRC which were either missing or found to require minor changes following the initial R1V4.10 release.  Also added newer versions of token.exe and instsrv.exe.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 7-28-97 R1V4 Checkpoint 10 Complete
\par \plain\f2\fs24 \tab \plain\f2\fs24\b 
\par 7-28-97 CDSV enhancement, misc. fixes (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added the ability to do CDS log recovery to a select set of tables rather than the entire database.  This is accomplished by listing the tables to recover in the apply log file.  See the CDS notes for more information on this feature. Files: cdsv.c, rollfor.c, rollback.c, cdsinit.c, cdslog.c, logread.c \endash  PTR#95111103
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a recently introduced problem where CDS would not properly recover a replace with index change. Rollfor.c
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem where CDS would not process rollbacks during recovery. Rollback.c
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem where CDS would complain of a bad log when applying a log that contained create table commands. Logread.c
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-28-97 RT.DLL "Document Author/DDSpec print crash" Fix (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that causes a crash when attempting to print a document or specification from the IBAE to a network printer connected to a Windows 95 machine.  Fixed NULL pointer in the print_package routine in execprt.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-28-97 RT.DLL "CDS exit crash" Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that causes a crash on exit from rt after failing to connect to CDS.  Changed call to cmstats_print() from rt.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-18-97 RT.DLL AUXPRINT failed, Error 122 on GetPrinter() call Fix (rwf)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed buffer size: changed from static size of 1000 bytes to size of PRINT_INFO_2 structure so that buffer size is sufficient for data returned from GetPrinter() call.
\par \pard\li360\plain\f2\fs20 File: execprt.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-18-97 RT.DLL "COMM SET_EVENT" Fix (lp)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed "COMM SET_EVENT" to check resource type against argument resource and not global comm resource.  This prevents the NO SUPPORT error message box when combining the legacy ONA comms and the SNA LUA comm in a single system.
\par \pard\li360\plain\f2\fs20 File: cm_ev.c. PTR # 97062603.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-18-97 CDSV.exe Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug which caused a NOT match operation to become a MATCH operation when the pattern was a simple string with no pattern characters.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-18-97 ODB.dll Change (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Left zero fill FT_NUMERIC fields when moving column values to fields.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Updated the odb.doc to note that the driver used must support the ODBC 2 API.   A driver that supports only the ODBC 3 API is not compatible.   The ODBC 3 driver manager\plain\f2\fs20\b\i  is \plain\f2\fs20 compatible.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-17-97 RT.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}changed catastrophe() function in execcds.c to allow adjusting down to server's interface level.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug which caused a NOT match operation to become a MATCH operation when the pattern was a simple string with no pattern characters.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-15-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed Unhandled Exception error that was caused by a CALL CSR statement when the CSR routine was defined but did not exist.  File: pcl.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-11-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed incompatibility between P+ and Mosaic.  If 'ppluscompatible' is set to 1 (Ddproj.ini), then relief buttons aren't grayed when they're disabled.  Now they are not redrawn when they are enabled or disabled.  File: mouse.c, pcl.c.  PTR #97062401.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The autoIME and ALLOWDUP field flag support was forgotten in ofb\\pcl2xxx.c and has been added.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug where a character would be ignored if tabbing into an amount field that had a leading minus sign.  File: datacoll.c.  PSR# 20-1487.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-8-97 moa\\src\\MAKEFILE change (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed CDS package specific makes and moved them to MakeCDS  to avoid getting the wrong part numbers.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-8-97 BC.EXE Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused an access violation when OFB source file contains an include path name greater than 80 characters.  File: compile.c.  PTR #97062501.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for '-F' option.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Improved error and warning return values passed back to the shell.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-02-97 Osql.exe Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Improved the Usage: statement result from "Osql -?" to better explain -F option.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Default DSN is now "CDS" concatenated with MOACURPROJ from registry, if any.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-02-97 CDSODBC Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Quoted column name aliases are allowed.  For example: SELECT myint AS 'my little integer' FROM table_T
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-1-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added RT usage information for OLE automation. Files: \\moa\\src\\include\\res.h, \\moa\\src\\nls\\english.rc, \\moa\\src\\rt\\rt.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-30-97 ODB.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed MAJOR memory leak problem in all query processing.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added new function, DBfreeEnv() to call SQLFreeEnv() and release the environment control block.   This function also calls DBdisconnect() for all open connections on the environment.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed minor memory leaks in DBqclose() and DBdisconnect().
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in handling FT_INT fields in dynaset updates.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-27-97 RT minor fix for building CDS requests (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The logic for building joins for CDSV could miscount the buffer by a byte.  This would only create a problem when the join was larger than the buffer space available to build the request. Files: rtable.c, PTR# 96053101
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-26-97 CDSV minor fixes/enhancements (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}out file now contains explicit message when NT application event log is full. File: cdsfatal.c
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed an obscure problem that could cause a cds 1855 error.  Problem would happen when RT has an empty FIXED field (defined with no decimal places \endash  eg: 5.0), increments the field by 0.5, and attempts to insert it into CDS. File: tablist.c, PTR# 96050601
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-25-97 IMPORT.EXE / EXPORT.EXE Fixes (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Descriptors now import and export Line Feed, Carriage Return, Horiz. Tab, and double quotes correctly.  Files: import.c, export.c.  PTR #97061701 and 97062301.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-25-97 CDS client change (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}cds_udp_port() now returns a negative if it fails rather than calling an exit function (ersysn()).  So now calling programs should check for an error and handle it.  The function cds_udp_port() is exposed in cdscl.dll.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-25-97 CDS install fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Close the program group window before finishing so it won't obscure the completion message.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 6-24-97 CDS and CDSODBC R1V4 Checkpoint 9 Complete\tab \plain\f2\fs24\b 
\par 6-23-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused DRAW FIELD (with Ddproj.INI EDITFIELDS=1) and DRAW MLTEXT to truncate part of the field when running on NT 4.  File: textedit.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-20-97 CDS install fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Run Drop-1A.exe on NT machines to get rid of control-Z characters at the end of \\etc\\services before running svrcfg.exe to update that file.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug in Win95 execution of svrcfg.exe that caused it to crash when options button was hit.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added msvcrt.dll to install list.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Put a better message out from svrcfg when TCP/IP configuration is flawed.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-20-97 CDS fix for more recovery problems (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Don't crash rolling forward a drop table when the table to be dropped already doesn't exist.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow three days of out file instead of only two before discarding it on open.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-19-97 RT.DLL Fix (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}RT debugger was unable to display or modify fields that were passed as parameters. This was repaired in the rt\\single.c file.  This defect was referenced in PTR 97012802.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}RT debugger would cause memory fault when the "P" option was selected when not all the local fields within a subroutine had been allocated. If the two local variables were defined within a subroutine and after the first had been allocated and the "P" operation was selected from the single step command line, RT would commit a segmentation violation. This defect was referenced in PTR 97061802.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-17-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Turn the FIELD FOCUS back on when a control (pushbutton, radiobutton, etc) is released.  PTR# 97061302  File: rtwindow.c.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Properly update display when controls are modified with HIDECONTROL and SHOWCONTROL.  PTR# 97061203.  File: scrlist.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-16-97 CDS fix for duplicate record problem (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem where CDServer could create duplicate records in the database.  The specific problem occurred when CDS recovered after a record replace followed by a replace with index change on the same record.  CDS compression can be used to remove the duplicate records after the index is rebuilt.  PTR# 97052901, files: rollfor.c
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-11-97 IBAE-SPECPAD.exe Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Tabs and CR/LFs are no longer removed from Notes.  File: specpad\\specview.cpp.  PTR# 97060202.\plain\f2\fs20\ul 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-11-97 SVRCFG (CDS configurator) Fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problems dealing with service name suffixes\plain\f2\fs20\ul 
\par \plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Use lower case for CDS section names in ddproj.ini
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-10-97 ODB.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem with single digit FT_NUMERIC fields updating numeric(1) columns.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed (or worked around) update problem with decimal(1,1) columns.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-6-97 QL.exe Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow the date value "0" for backward compatibility.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-6-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \plain\f2\fs20 Fixed "Examine Mode" display of a subroutine when one or more local fields are declared within the subroutine.  File: rt\\single.c.\plain\f2\fs20\ul 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b 6-5-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Cut, Copy and Paste for TextEdit fields have been enhanced to work correctly.  Cut and Copy extract field data from the editted selection, and Paste only allows data of the correct type to be inserted into the destination field.  Cut, Copy and Paste can be invoked from the Ctl-X, Ctl-C and Ctl-V key combinations, and by a right button mouse click while over the TextEdit field.  PTR# 97052701  Files: datacoll.c, textedit.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-05-97 CDS Fix (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem in CDS where CDS would terminate with an out file message: Caught signal 21 and Terminated by signal 21.  This problem was related to a user signing off of the server sometime after compression was run.  PTR# 97060402.  Files: cdscmprs.c
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-05-97 CSR.DLL Fix (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The OFB function PROC_LIST function F_CLEAR and F_CLEARARRAY failed to clear two dimension arrays correctly. In the case of the F_CLEAR function it failed to clear any MEMBER's that followed the failed array. This has been corrected in the function do_unary_field within csr/proclist.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 6-04-97 CDSODBC Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug of ignoring pcbValue parameter to SQLBindParameter() when it doesn't indicate NULL VALUE.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow setup choice of not installing dictionary tools that are included in RT package.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug in setting DISTINCT switch on SELECT projection lists
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-30-97 RT.DLL Fix (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed memory access error related to overwriting malloc pointers in string copy of multi language  strings. The error was located in the str2field function of the moa\\src\\misc\\convers.c file.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 BitEdit/IcnEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed string references for 'Bit Map' to 'Bitmap'.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed author gets into invalid state when launched from Screen Author.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bogus Help IDs for Create and Create/Browse dialogs.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a palette to the bitmap header used for a new bitmap. Previously, no palette was specified, which no longer works properly with MS Paint.  The palette used is the one from the current project's .ini file.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 Browser Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed a resource ID (IDS_BROW_WINTWITLE) that was conflicting with string resources in other authors at runtime.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in browser caused when user enters a new filter and the changes focus by selecting an item in the list box with the mouse which is at a higher index in the list box and will not exist after the filter is applied.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed spaces between application name and object (i.e. now its common:startup) which showed in name pane when * (i.e. all) applications are selected.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug that caused the item name to be wrong when trying to launch the author for an object when '*' was selected for the application.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 DDobj Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug in the operator ==.  It's checking const type even if the reference type is not constant.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a -I parameter to the compile in Project New so the compiler can find the keys.h file in src\\include.  Also, the compile output now goes to a file (newproj.log) in the new project directory.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a potential infinite loop:  Added Change Notes which does a SetNotes without the DDWrite.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed logic in 'GetNotes' so notes are never read if object is invalid. Original problem was described as not being able to save notes for new objects that were just created.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed logic in 'GetPath' so paths are never read if object is invalid.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 DDSpec Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for new field flag 'autoIME' added to RT 1.4.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified to allow notes for fields from an application different than from the current screen's application to be printed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified to allow notes for Combofields to be printed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified rt initialization logic and initialized globals when 'ddspec' is called from command line (i.e. entry point of main).
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified common application in the minimal dictionary so that default compiled lists required by the run time "print_package" routine are available.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 DocEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix for the cursor gets the 'jitters' problem. Added support for a sizing/moving cursor when cursor is over a object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Clear the saved Literal Text 'Caption' when initializing the Text dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed unused 'Color...' button from the 'Font Pitch' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed toolbar alignment and visibility problems.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem which caused IBAE to crash whenever an attempt to print a document was made without having a default printer assigned.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added negative array subscript validation for field arrays used as test objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}A drag-n-drop bitmap from the browser now gets a default size.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problems when resizing document for objects outside of the documents bounding area.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Restricted input to line width and height edit boxes to numeric only.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed menu ID problem which left the 'Notes' button enabled for new objects on the screen.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for 'Copy Notes Too' functionality in 'Save As' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed Tab-ordering problem when clicking on the same object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Replaced missing 'Multiple-insert' feature which was lost in 1.4.x. Note: Multi-insert is now done by pressing the 'Ctrl' key when selecting an object to insert either from the 'Insert' toolbar or menu.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Resolved several issues involving the 'Document' author.  Invalid toolbar for a given author.  Toolbar that would stay open or close unexpectedly.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'Align\\Size' menu to only enable if one or more non-anchor objects are sizable.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified field and graphic objects to correct a problem which caused IBAE to crash when attempting to 'Save Notes' in the standard 'Notes' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Created unique menu IDs for inserting text, lines, rectangles & graphics. This helps to avoid toolbar confusion when both the 'ScrEdit' & 'DocEdit' toolbars are active and docked.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 FldEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for new field flag 'autoIME' added to RT 1.4
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed a "return" that was left in by mistake, since revision 2.13
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The wrong string resource was being used for the window title \tab on the field 'SaveAs' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}If a change was made to one of a field's reference objects, and the save button is pressed before focus left the reference combo box, the change didn't get saved.  Added code to the ValidateAllEdits, called from Save/SaveAs, to ensure that the KillFocus event gets called for the current control. Also fixed a bug that caused an assertion error when the ValidateChoice routine gets called when the combo box has no selection.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 HcmEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added the ability to specify the name and or location of the 'eehllapi' DLL in the 'AuthorExe' section of the 'Ibae.ini' file.  The key name for this entry is 'Ehllapi DLL'.  If the entry  is not found in the ibae.ini file, then the default "eehllapi.dll" will be used just as it is now so no one will need to add this entry unless their situation requires it.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed the save function AGAIN--it now puts the separator in front again to be compatible with the way the OFB Author does it, but only if it's not the first routine in the file.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed case on a CRT Put Keys dialog help button.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added UpdateButtons to the end of the CRT button event, so the CRT PUT Keys button is properly disabled when the last item is selected.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed the way the parameter fields work in the edit dialogs.  The fields are now radio buttons that look like raised fields, so that the keyboard interface works nicely.  There is no more forcing of focus to the literal field.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The SaveAs function was never doing a compile, just saving the file! Also, the "Save Notes Too" checkbox in the SaveAs dialog is now hidden for the case when a new object is being saved.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The QuerySaveChanges function was saving the file before getting an object name, in the case of a new host comm object.  This caused the subroutine in the file to be called "Untitlted."  The "Yes" response to the query now simply calls OnFileSave, so everything goes as it should.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed LoadCppOptions to work like the OFB Author:  Appends the MOADIR include paths to any path found in the project's OFBCompileSettings.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed the left/right justify radio buttons to check boxes to allow neither to be selected, but selecting both at once is prevented.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}You can now edit comments or preprocessor statements without having to delete the objects first.  The "Insert" and "Delete" buttons are changed to say "Save" and "Cancel" and all other buttons are grayed out while editing the comment.  If the user makes a change to the comment and then attempts to cancel or to change focus to another line, the user will be prompted as to whether the changes are to be discarded.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The "Insert" button is no longer automatically disabled following an insert.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Subroutine divider line now added to the end of a routine instead of the beginning.  Compiler doesn't like a line at the front of a file, but allows one at the bottom.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Various problems and hangs when trying to save and compile when there are errors in the compilation. Was due to no "extern C" statement for the MREtoList function statement so program was going into la-la land and either hanging or just losing any error statements.  Also wrong DLL was being loaded (ofbedit.dll instead of hcmedit.dll).
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Bracket in wrong place caused a single fill or delim char to NOT be placed in the line at all.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Verb Type selection is not restored if CRT PUT KEY is in OFB statement. Also did some cleanup to remove references to non-existent resource buttons to prevent errors in the future.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Do not allow Put Keys choices to be inserted after the last line of an object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Double clicking on error message does not put cursor on the line in error if this OFB procedure is not the first in the file.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added the double-click event for the up/down arrow keys in the CRT dialog, to the message map.  This prevents the mouse clicks from seeming to "get lost."
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added an Undo function for changes to the map list box.  Also tightened up the enable/disable states of the buttons a bit. Also fixed a bug that was causing the subroutine divider line to get written to the top of a new file, which causes a compiler error!
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 IbaFrame Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The Import Bitmap dialog was saving the explicit path to the bitmap, rather than replacing the project path portion with "$PROJDIR".  Added a simple function to do this replacement.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Imported bitmaps through the 'Import Bitmap' dialog had their notes set to '### System Defined ###'.  This was caused by the import not clearing the forward referrence flag.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem which caused an error message 'Could not open project for DDE command' to appear after 'Cancel'ing the project open.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Propagate 'LaunchBrowser' wParam and lParam values to Browser after launch. This fixes a problem which caused the Browser to display the wrong object type after being launched by pressing the 'Browse' button in the Screen Author.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Consolidated the multiple "async_start?" functions to one reuseable one. Changed the launch of rt and specpad to confirm close project, then leave IBAE window showing and enabled.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added 'OnIdle' event processing to update the iconified MDI window position after a toolbar change.  This fixes a problem that sometimes causes an conified window to disappear when a toolbar at the bottom of the screen went away.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The F1 key will now invoke the help finder (index) instead of the help file contents page.  This is more useful and more standard.  The Help menu was changed slightly, to have 'Search...' on top (with the F1 accelerator) and 'Contents' second. Also changed the parent on the call to WinHelp to be the main frame window, so it no longer terminates when other apps close.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The F1 key shouldn't do help finder, as previously "fixed."  It should do context-sensitive help, bringing up the applicable help topic for the current context.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed text for IBAE Options tool tip.  (Previously said "Tools Options".)
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Shortened Welcome tip of the day (removed spacing) so it doesn't get cut off.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}OnCloseProject now calls CloseProject which returns a BOOL, false if user cancelled during QuerySaveChanges.  CloseProject is now called from checkCloseProject, allowing whatever called it to check for the Cancel request.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}In the CSR Map dialog, the Save button is no longer disabled when the map list is empty.  The "Variable" checkbox is now checked whenever the "# of Parameters" box contains "-1".  The arrow keys now update the fields as the selection changes in the CSR map.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified the "AddToolsToMenu" function so if the menu item isn't there (therefore ModifyMenu won't work), AppendMenu is called.  This handles the case where all the tool menu items got removed because no project was\tab open, then the modify fails so the tools never get added.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Created a base class for the three Import tools: CSR, BMP, ICN. They now look and act the same, they all delete mappings not in the list on Save.  Also added a column sort.  Clicking on any column heading sorts the list by that column, with reverse sort toggle, ala NT Explorer.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed the percent field in the "Attention Box" (the load progress screen) so it has a gray background to match the bitmap it's on, rather than the current window color.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified help IDs in 'HcmEdit' to resolve toolbar tip problems.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Adjusted Copyright line spacing in IBAE startup splash screen.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed IBAE Options windows title is now correct "IBAE Options".
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a check for return value on the first write to the project .INI file on exit.  If it fails, a message box informs the user.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added Copy... and Notes... buttons to the Open Object dialog.  This allows access to Notes on any object and allows a copy to be made of any object.  Several reported PSRs are fixed by this change.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed toolbar dialog (View\\toolbar) and context menu (right mouse over toolbars) to be consistent in displaying and not displaying toolbars.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed tooltips and status bar messages for browser dialog bar.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added Help id for button on View\\toolbar dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added "Variable" check box to the Import CSRs dialog to support the variable parameters option.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed the text used in a message box in the Import CSR Utility. Needed to clarify the action taken for OK when changes had been made and not committed to the table.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Moved the Import CSRs and Import BMPs menu items from the Project menu to the Tools menu, under "Import".
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Import CSR dialog now deletes "Removed" entries on Save. No longer quits with a bad name error.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}No longer transposes OFB and CSR names on a save. List is now sorted. Duplicate entries are now prevented.  Added a picklist of csr.dll function names to the Import CSR dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed tab order and button enabling problems related to above fixes.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Project-New got broken when I changed the files and directory structure of the minimal dictionary.  Fixed that and also the include path to keys.h in the ofb.ofb file in the minimal dict.  It needs to be relative to the project directory rather than the file.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Help now goes to the correct topic for IBAE Options (used to go to Project Options.)
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 IbaMinDD Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed some leading spaces to tabs in ofb.ofb file to fix bad alignment in OFB Author.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Rebuilt minimum data dictionary with combo icon.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added combo icon.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}New required fields for CDS/ODBC had been added as a new file newflds), but not compiled into ibamindd dictionary because the makedd.bat file wasn't updated to import the new file.  Added the new fields to the existing "fld" file and removed the "newflds" file.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added to the set of objects included in the minimal dictionary \tab and changed file names and directory structure to be AIMS-compatible.  Updated makemin.bat accordingly
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 JdmEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}A 'Report with Fields' (*.RPT) file should be created from the JetForm Designer for use with the JetForm Data Map.  An MDF file will still work (a 'compiled form') UNLESS compiled for Windows Printing. Error handling was improved.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added drag/drop support from Browser and launch-by-reference support to the two item fields.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 LstEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added object name to the 'Get Edit Procedure' dialog title.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed code that attempted to launch obsolete 'superpad.exe'.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Close author window after running Edit Procedure, and or Save/Cancel.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed several bugs that had to do with opening a text edit window to create or edit LST object source.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 MnuEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Restored two bitmaps used in the Access Flag picklist for flag on and flag off.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 OfbEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The new GetItemDlg now has an optional "CopyNotesToo" parameter that can hide the Copy Notes checkbox if false.  A couple of ofbprof's calls were changed to change the optional parameter to False where it didn't make sense to copy notes (as in a New object dialog).
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 PdmEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed lots of problems related to the attempt to connect a PDM that causes recursion, changing menu focus when current object definition is invalid, and other similar stuff.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a static variable to hold the CWnd pointer to the author window. The variable is checked in the UpdateObject event so it can ignore any update messages from itself.  This prevents the need to close up the menu on a save.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added Update Object support for descriptors and language change.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The font used for the menu text in the author now uses the system menu font set in Control Panel, Display, and responds dynamically to font changes.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed the initial state of a new menu item's caption from "Undefined" to an empty literal.  This solves the problem of the saved "lastLiteral" from remaining after a Cancel.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 PlhEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem which resulted in the desired picklist font not being saved.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}No longer require object to be named before doing properties dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed refresh problem when used in layout
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed TopLeft, Top & Left unused sizing handles.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 ScrEdit Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for creating a new bitmap or launching the bitmap author for a new bitmap from within the common property pages. This allows top down development to be performed using screens and bitmaps.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix for the cursor gets the 'jitters' problem. Added support for a sizing/moving cursor when cursor is over a object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow screen to refresh after INI file updates for the project.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed toolbar alignment and visability problems.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed multi-language strings (MLS) label sizing problem. Added MLS string support to pushbuttons, radiobuttons & checkboxes.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Replaced system font dialog with a new modal font dialog that supports the Transparent attribute.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Disabled 'Author' button on the common property page for 'TAG' & 'CSR' objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Disabled 'Create' button on the common property page for 'CSR' objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Enabled 'Create' button on the common property page for 'CSR' objects. 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'Graphic' object to not set objects default size.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'Combofield' object to allow all data dictionary objects to be optional with the exception of the field reference which is required.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'Checkbox' object to not display the invalid field object error message twice when doing a 'OnOK' or 'OnApply' processing.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added 'QuerySaveChanges' method to property sheets to check for modified property sheet pages OnClose of the property sheet or Saving the screen.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}A drag-n-drop bitmap from the browser now gets a default size.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added ability to verify constant field array subscripts.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problems when resizing screen for objects outside of the screens bounding area.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix for 'OnApply' button disables after focus change.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix for checkbox validation does not occur for 'OnOK'.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for 'Transparency' to most Screen Author objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added new 'Position' dialog page to all Screen Author objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed menu ID problem which left the 'Notes' button enabled for new objects on the screen.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for 'Copy Notes Too' functionality in 'Save As' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed Tab-ordering problem when clicking on the same object.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added missing 'Multiple-insert' feature which was lost in 1.4.x. Note: Multi-insert is now done by pressing the 'Ctrl' key when selecting an object to insert either from the 'Insert' toolbar or menu.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for setting position and size information for the PIC header object. This was done using the new object position dialog page that was added to all screen objects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Resolved several issues involving the 'Screen', 'Layout' and 'Pick-list Header' authors.  Invalid toolbars for a given author.  Toolbars that would stay open or close unexpectedly.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified Pick List Author to correct a problem which caused IBAE to crash when attempting to 'Save Notes' in the standard 'Notes' dialog.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified so that the screen background is always displayed by IBAE.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix for Tab Order not working. Note: Applies to 'Document Author' also.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'Align\\Size' menu to only enable if one or more non-anchor objects are sizable.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified label object to correctly reset style properties on 'Cancel'.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified 'IsValidObject' member function of 'checkbox' object to ensure the field type is of type 'FLAGS'.  This prevents a screen with an invalid checkbox from being saved to the data dictionary.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed 'Bit Map' to 'Bitmap' in resource file.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 SpecPad Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for new field flag 'autoIME' added to RT 1.4
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified to allow notes for fields from an application different than from the current screen's application to be displayed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified to allow notes for Combofields to be displayed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed Help to be more consistent with IBAE Authors:  The Help menu has both "Contents" and "Search...", and the F1 key invokes "Contents."
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed SpecPad F1 help for dialogs.  "What's this?" style help is now used in all dialogs.  Help button in Options dialog brings up help finder.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed some help ID numbers so they don't conflict with Word Pad help.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 7-08-97 Tool Changes (rfk)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs18 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a function to the Sheet so a backout changes can be done without dismissing the properties window. Added a flag to the common property page to prevent ApplyChanges from getting called from both OnItemSelect and the lost focus event.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Made the "Copy Notes" checkbox optional in the GetItemDlg class.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified the common property page to ignore the return value from CDialog::OnInitDialog (as per MFC documentation).
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added code to check and ask to save changes when the system close button is used on the Notes dialog.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 5-28-97 RT R1V4 Checkpoint 9 Complete\tab \plain\f2\fs24\b 
\par 5-28-97 CDS Fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem that caused crash in cdsv.exe when project name was longer than 30 characters.\plain\f2\fs20\ul 
\par \plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed package to not install msvcrt40.dll, to avoid problems on Win95.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in svrcfg.exe and svrcfgh.dll, the CDS configuration utility.  Made enhancements suggested by John Lowry.
\par \pard\li720\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Provide a pick list for project name, based on subdirectories of MOAPROJDIR.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Hide advanced options unless called for by the user.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Show previously configured advanced options when reconfiguring a server.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bugs in showing previously configured UDP port number.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-23-97 OSQL.exe Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem that caused failure of cdscolumns function when the current default application was not "common".\plain\f2\fs20\ul 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-23-97 CDSODBC.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem with last digit of values input from FT_FIXED fields.  This problem caused 99.999 input from a fixed (5,3) field to be inserted as 99.990 in a numeric(5,3) column.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed package to not install msvcrt40.dll, to avoid problems on Win95.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-23-97 ODB.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed problem with last digit of values input from FT_FIXED fields.  This problem caused 99.999 input from a fixed (5,3) field to be inserted as 100.00 in a numeric(5,2) column.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-22-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Button text with & (&&) as part of the text caused part of text to be cut off when displayed..  File changed: /moa/src/dsplist/tdspl.c, /moa/src/rt/mouse.c.  PTR #97051402.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}PAGEUP now navigates correctly between data collect screens even when the screens are displayed from different OFB routines.  Files changed: /moa/src/include/rt.h, rtprotos.h, /moa/src/rt/pcl.c, pclsubs.c.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The OFB SINGLESTEP DEBUGGER now displays the current OFB routine on the prompt line.  Files changed: /moa/src/rt/single.c, debug.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-19-97 ODB.DLL  enhancements (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The list parameter to the following functions may be passed in an indirect field object:
\par \pard\li1080\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}DBmultiDisplay();
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}DBretrieve();
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}DBcreateDynasetLst();
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}DBcreateQueryLst();
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}DBinsertLst().
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-15-97 CDS & RT header modules (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed cds_errno from rtdef.h.  It is no longer exported.  Use clenv.h instead.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Removed cds_errno as an export from cdserror.h.   It is no longer exported, as of checkpoint 8.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}There is a new function, CdsErrNo(clenv *env), exported by cdscl.dll, which returns the cds_errno value for an environment.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-13-97 CDS ODBC (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Applied MS service pack of 4/25/97 to ODBC driver manager modules installed with CDS driver.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 5-12-97 R1V4 Checkpoint 8 Complete\tab 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b 5-12-97 ODB.DLL  bug fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused error 5494, "out of buffer space" on an insert or update with many numeric fields.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-08-97 CDS ODBC (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for ANSI SQL join syntax for outer joins.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in SQLTransact that cause failure when the environment handle parameter was NULL.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed driver package setup to use ODBC 3.0 driver manager and attendant software.  CDS ODBC driver is still at ODBC version 2.5.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Setup now works from remote unmapped drives.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 5-05-97 GREETER.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in CDS error logic, related to not converting to new CDS API.  Changed biocdsdb.cpp.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in returning address of CDS field data in the stack. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-30-97 PUTREG.EXE Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed access privilege requirements for using putreg.exe to update the registry.  Putreg.exe no longer requires admin privilege in order to update the local registry.  File changed: /moa/src/utility/putreg.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-30-97 DDXREF.EXE Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed cross reference builds of Pull Down Menu (PDM) data dictionary objects where the item number exceeds 127.  File changed: /moa/src/utility/ddxref.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-30-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}During initialization, RT now sets the locale to the regional setting of the workstation.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/rt.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-30-97 RT.DLL Fix (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The stretch field logic incorporated in the draw field section of exec draw was added to local print.  There may be a difference in the number of pixels required in screen operations and printer operations. If local printing of fields utilizing proportional fonts is an important part of an application, test and calibrate various values of stretchfiled in ddproj.ini. Files changed: /moa/src/include/textedit.h /moa/src/rt/textedit.c /moa/srxc/rt/execdraw.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-29-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed console window output bug on Win 95 workstations for applications that invoke the CSR:create_process.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/rt.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-29-97 CDS ODBC (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in returning SQL_LOCK_TYPES from SQLGetInfo().
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-25-97 RTEXE & RTCLIENT.DLL Enhancement (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added versioning into the distributable files of rt.exe and rtclient.dll such that MI and the explorer see the file versioning compiled into the files.  Files changed: /moa/src/rtserver/makefile, /moa/src/rtserver/rtserver.rc, /moasrc/rtserver/rtexe_v.rc, /moa/src/rtclient/makefile, /moa/src/rtclient/rtclient/rtclient.rc, /moa/src/rtclient/rtcli_v.rc.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-23-97 DIBAPI.DLL Enhancement (rjn/cy)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added ability to capture to a file.  File changed: /moa/src/prtscdll/capture.c.  PTR# none. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-21-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug where the error message box would display "Visitor Queue Error" instead of "Error" in the title bar.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/errorbox.c.  PTR# 97022001. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-16-97 IBAE scredit.dll Enhancement (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support in the screen author for personality switch: ppluscompatible (ddproj.ini).  When bit 1 is set, borderless fields are drawn without the extra pixel surrounding the field to be compatibly with Release 5.  File changed: /moa/src/include/rtdef.h, rt/rt.def, /moa/ibasrc/scredit/field.cpp.  PTR #97030701. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-16-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed the display of the default time and status line string location.  When the version information string increased it caused the rightmost digits to be rendered outside the normal RT window area.  The starting X-coordinate was modified such that all version numbers will be displayed.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/io.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-15-97 RT.DLL Fix (bhs)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Enhanced winhelp csr to support windows 95 style help.  Default behavior is to display help contents as in previous versions.  To invoke table of contents using HELP_FINDER (windows 95 style) rather than HELP_CONTENTS use the WH_OPTION option with WH_FINDER as parameter 2 and the third parameter is 1 or 0 (1=enabled).   Also added WH_POPUP to tell winhelp to display field level help in a popup window rather than bringing the whole help manual forward.  This option can be set by calling winhelp with WH_OPTION as the first parameter, WH_POPUP as the second parameter and the third parameter is 1 or 0 (1=enabled).  Finally, added the ability to read #includes from the MAP section or the .hpj file when generating the topic list.  This provides better compatibility with robohelp's format.  Files changed /moa/src/csr/winhelp.c and /moa/src/include/ofb/winhelp.h
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-14-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed warning issued by linker concerning the definition of LanguageSep and LanguageIndex.  Files changed: /moa/src/include/rtdef.h and /moa/src/include/convers.h. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-11-97 RT.DLL Fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug when COMBOVERIFY is invoked and the associated picklist has no header.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/pclsubs.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-11-97 RT.DLL OFB Debugger Enhancement (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The console window is brought to the foreground when the OFB single step debugger is envoked.  RTs main window is brought to the foreground when you exit single step mode.  ETR #96111206.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/pcl.c, single.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-8-97 CDS & CDS ODBC V1.4.7 Checkpoint Created
\par \pard\li360\fi-360\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-8-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug where the cursor was left in the wrong MLFIELD if RT lost focus (Message Box).  PTR #97030303.  File changed: /moa/src/rt/datacoll.c. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-8-97 CDS Setup Change(s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}WordView is no longer installed with CDS server or CDS ODBC driver packages.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-7-97 CDS Table Rename When Using Multiple CDServers (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}When renaming a table while connecting to multiple CDServers, a duplicate table error would be reported if the new table name existed on ANY of the CDServers.  Changed so that the name only has to be unique on the server with the table that is being renamed.  File: clstubs.c
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-7-97 QL.EXE Data Length Validation (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}ql has been changed to validate the length of data being inserted into CDS.  The default action for data larger than the defined field size is to report an error.  Optionally, ql can be set to truncate the excess data or to ignore the length validation and allow the data into CDS. Files changed: ql.h, ql.c, qldml.c, qlaux.c.  PTR# 97030504 
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Minor change to allow specific index to be displayed on table using named service specification (show indexes on service:table).  Files: ql.c, PTR#: 97032401
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 4-4-97 RT.DLL Edit Pattern Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}NUMCHARS should now be correct for all field types when using DRAW MLFIELD.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The hyphen character in an ASCII field would cause erratic cursor movement if the edit pattern also had a hyphen in it.  
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Leading zeros were being discarded in NUMERIC fields for "NNN" edit patterns.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Negative numbers can now be cut and pasted.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\datacoll.c, textedit.c.  PTR #97021803, 97031102, 97032801.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 04-03-97 CDS fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Created new version of .mak file for svrcfg.exe to finally get the right version info included.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 04-02-97 Version Information Display fix (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed binary file version display.  File changed: \\moa\\src\\c_utils\\vcbump.c
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Improved alignment of displayed version information for both console and GUI tools.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 04-02-97 CDSV change (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Create a debug map from the link of cdsv.exe and put it in the distribution.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-28-97 Dynamic Pick List Fixes (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Pick list vertical sizing errors. Fixes PTR 97022801
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Pick list horizontal sizing with proportional fonts was in error. Fixes PTR 97021001
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-26-97 CDS ODBC Fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Got rid of translator options when adding a data source.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed tab order in "add data source" dialog.  Fixes PSR # 3837.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-21-97 CDS Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}When cdsv is started from the command line it shows a minimized window only unless the command line option \plain\f2\fs20\b \endash W\plain\f2\fs20  is used.  This addresses PSR# 3968.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-20-97 ODB.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in handling FT_NUMERIC fields with maximum length values.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Return \endash DB77 when expected.   Fixes PSR # 3826.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-20-97 CDS prcapture bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed print of statistics evoked by the \endash s command line option by using vsprintf() instead of wvsprintf() in misc\\hexdmp.c.   Only vsprintf() supports the %f format.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Get ticks per second from capture file, if available, so prcapture can accurately show the time used per function at the original server machine.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-18-97 CDS Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added LIST option to cdinstsv.exe.  This is an abbreviated list of the VIEW info plus showing the UDP port number used. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-17-97 CDS Setup Fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe and svrcfgh.dll to accept only a full path for the cds recovery log file.   This fixes PSR 4000.   The program now tries to show the option previously chosen when re-configuring.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe handling of UDP port numbers so that the existing previously configured port number for a server is preserved unless explicitly overridden by the developer.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe handling of UDP port numbers so that if a user specifies an existing previously configured port number for a different server, that user gets a warning message and a chance to reconsider the port number.  This fixes PSR #4005.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe to insist on a valid project name.  This fixes PSR #4037.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-17-97 CDS ODBC Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for SQL ALTER TABLE statement to allow developers to add or drop column definitions for a table.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}ALTER TABLE with ADD column is now supported for variable schema tables to allow use with third party reporting tools like Crystal Reports and MS Access.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-12-97 SCREDIT.DLL Enhancement (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for DRAW TITLE verb.  When a screen is opened the DRAW TITLE is converted to a DRAW TEXT and a DRAW BOX.  MultiLanguage Strings are not supported in the conversion.  Files changed: \\iba\\src\\scredit\\title.cpp, title.hpp.  PTR# 97010701.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-12-97 cdsstat.exe Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added option "\endash C" to show count of current connections.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-12-97 ql.exe Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added SLEEP verb for use in testing scripts.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-12-97 Osql.exe Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added SLEEP verb for use in testing scripts.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-12-97 ODB.DLL Fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bugs in setting column precision, especially for timestamp data.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added to dberrs.h #define MOA_PUT_EMPTY_STRING_AS_NULL 2202, option ID for DBsetConnectOption().
\par \pard\li360\fi-360\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b\ul 3-12-97 R1V4 Checkpoint 7 Complete\tab 
\par \plain\f2\fs24\b 3-10-97 RT.DLL International Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for DEAD CHARACTERS, diacritics, for Spanish and Thai.  Characters received by the WM_KEYDOWN message are sent back to the WndProc via TranslateMessage() and processed as WM_CHAR messages.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\datacoll.c, rtwindow.c, textedit.c.  PTR #97020601.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-10-97 Osql.exe  changes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow semi-colon at end of tables, sqltables, and types requests.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Honor 'commit', 'rollback' and 'begin work' requests.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-7-97 AuxPrint Enhancement  in verifone.exe (dlw)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added retries for CreateFile() on COM port.  This allows it to start automatically when JetForm temporarily has the port open.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-5-97 CDSV Running as Service Fix (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem where CDSV would fail to run as a service, reporting event information related to a different project than expected for the service.  PTR 97012302, Files: cdsv.c, start.c
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 03-05-97 CDSODBC.dll - Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for inserting mulitple records, using bound parameter arrays.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for ODBC API function SQLParamOptions() as a part of the array insert support.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 03-04-97 ODB.dll - Enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}New client side option MOA_PUT_EMPTY_STRING_AS_NULL for DBsetConnectOption().  The default is FALSE, meaning FT_ASCII fields with empty string values are set to the database as a zero length string.  The trouble with this is that SQL-Server silently converts empty strings to single character blank strings.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 3-4-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug in MultiLanguage String logic for CDS Extract, PickList and Pickverify verbs.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\misc\\convers.c.  PTR #97012801.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}TE fields without an edit pattern now beep when full.  File changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\datacoll.c.  PTR #97010703.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}TE fields respond correctly to the DC_FUNC_BAD key.  This was broken in R1V3C7.  PTR #97022702.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-28-97 CDS import and export fix/enhancement (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Modified cdsimprt and cdsexprt to support connection to multiple servers.  See cds notes for more details on this feature.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added -T switch to cdsimprt to allow truncation of ascii and numeric data that exceeds defined field size.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Made cdsexprt and cdsimprt compatible with previous versions.  Old export files can be imported on current version and export files from current version can be imported on older versions.  Files: imexport.h, cdsimprt.c, cdsexprt.c.  For PTRs: 97022703, 97022704, 97020501, 97012902.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-28-97 CDS setup bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed cdinstsv.exe to prevent install when MOAPROJDIR is a remote drive or a RAM drive.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed cdsv.exe to prevent logging of superfluous start and stop events.  In particular "StartServiceCtrlDispatcher failed" information is no longer written.  It wasn't helpful.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-27-97 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Postpone checking for server running on designated machine to allow a mix of machine for different service name suffixes with the same dictionary.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused crash in CDS ODBC driver when selecting with a very long projection list.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-27-97 CDS ODBC Enhancements (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow smalldatetype as a column data-type, meaning DATE
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow column definition option of NULL, which the default, meaning 'allow null value'.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}support error SQLState 21S01 when insert values list doesn't match the column list.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Give a more explicit error message when user tries to update current of cursor when that cursor was not defined with a FOR UPDATE clause in the select statement.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-27-97 CDS prcaptur.exe bug fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused failure when -S option was used in the command line.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-25-97 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Use exclusive record update locks on ODBC fetches when reading on an updatable context within a LUW, when the SQL_TXN_ISOLATION option is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED (the default) or higher.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Use exclusive lock inside the server when reading for Update_All() and currently in a LUW and current connection option for concurrency is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED.  That option setting is the default for users of the CDS ODBC driver.   Users of the old interface may set that option too, via SetConnectOption(), but their default is SQL_TXN_READ_UNCOMMITTED.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Wrap the update in a LUW whenever not already in a LUW and the update is a Cds_Update_All() that could affect more than one record.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Set proper SQLState for bad option ID and bad option parm value for SQLSetConnectOption.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Make sure that SQL_TXN_ISOLATION option default value at the server is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED.   (For ODBC clients only).
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added support for updating a column  to NULL value from ODBC.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Return correct SQLState when given a bad table name on an ODBC INSERT statement.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Return correct SQLState when given a bad primary key for an insert or a bad secondary key for any update.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-24-97 CDS QL bug fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Adjust at run time to not use batch insert on insert from select when the server can't handle it.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-21-97 CDS crash on find_n (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a problem where CDS could crash on find_n if a previous find_n on the same context failed for some reason.  The example used to produce the failure was encountering an exclusive locked record. Files changed: cdsfind.c. PTR #97021301
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-21-97 CDS bug fix (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that prevented the closing of a pseudo-connection created during restart general recovery for rollback of an incomplete LUW.   Changed only ccb.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 2-19-97 RT.DLL msgbox verb (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The wait cursor is now reset before displaying a Message Box (OFB MSGBOX verb).  Files changed: moa\\src\\rt\\pcl.c.  PTR #96102304.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-14-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Requests for EXCLUSIVE record locks are silently downgraded to simple update locks when the lock requests are outside of a Logical Unit of Work.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}CDS ODBC SQL now supports insert from a query spec as well as from a values list.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-13-97 RT.DLL Enhancements (dlw)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Picks built-in printer fonts with italic and underline attributes more accurately.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added logic to minimize effects of a bug in Microsoft's RASDD.DLL which sometimes caused double underlines when printing to the PR50.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-13-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Ordinal numbers in SQL 'ORDER BY' clauses are now supported.  The ordinal number must refer to a column in the projection list.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 2-11-97 IBAE OFBEDIT.DLL / HCMEDIT.DLL (rjn/bm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Messages generated by the OFB compiler are now added to the compile output listbox instead of being discarded.  Files changed: ibasrc\\ofbedit\\ofbcomp.cpp,ofbcomp.h, ibasrc\\hcmedit\\ofbcomp.cpp,ofbcomp.h.  PTR #96123001, PSR #3573.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-11-97 New CSRs (nrn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added sacombopv CSR to work with combo fields in addition to sacombopl.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-11-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added batch insert function to client and server.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed QL to use batch insert when inserting from a selected context.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed CDSODBC driver to use batch insert for every insert.  The normal batch size is one.  The batch may contain as many records as will fit in one 64K buffer.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow multiple VALUES lists on an SQL insert statement to create multiple rows with one statement.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow TEXT as a data type specifier in a create table statement.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow user to use dictionary fields from up to 7 different dictionary applications, within a single SQL statement, such as CREATE TABLE.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 2-10-97 RT.DLL Calculator Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug that caused an access violation when trying to insert a calculator value, that is too large, into the current field.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\calc.c.  PTR #97013001.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 2-7-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug that caused invalid results to be returned from an exponentation operation on FIXED fields when the Decimal Insertion character (INIT 23) was set to something other than '.'.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\expr.c.  PTR #97020603.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 02-06-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added multi-thread support.   The driver is now 'thread safe'.  Fixes PSR 4011.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Detect and report invalid date literals in SQL 'where' clauses.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Cleanup up some other error reporting to return the correct SQLState.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Change parser to allow table_name.index name in DROP INDEX table_name.index_name.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-31-97 CDS Two-Phase Commit Fixes (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Made fixes necessary for NT CDServer to pass the two-phase commit tests in the CDS regression test suite.  Prior to these changes, CDS would fail on all two phase commit or rollback attempts.  Changed both CDS and RT. Files: clstubs.c, cmfparms.c, cdslog.c, cds.c, ccb.c, svdofunc.c, svsvproc.h, svinit.c, svunpack.c, servnt.c, server.c, svsetup.c.  PTR 96112001, 97011401.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-31-97 CDS 873 Causes RT to Crash (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed RT to not catastrophe on CDS 873 errors.  Application is now responsible for checking for such errors and taking appropriate action.  File: execcds.c, clstusbs.c.  PTR 96120601
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-31-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added function SQLNativeSql().  If the parser likes a statement it will return it via SQLNativeSql.   You still can't see what goes to server execept through prcaptur.exe.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed parser to recognize GRANT statements.  Nothing is done with them but now scripts with GRANTs in them can be executed without error.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-30-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}don't release the context created for an insert and don't create a new CDS context when the existing stmt->contxt will work for an insert.  This speeds performance on insert.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Announce that only one connection per user is allowed via SQLGetInfo(SQL_ACTIVE_CONNECTIONS).
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 1-28-97 RT.DLL Fix (rjn)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Allow characters > 0x80 to be processed in a TE FIELD.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\datacoll.c.  PTR # 97012803.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 LOGDUMP utility fix (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The CDS logdump utility would crash or report incorrect information when processing some 2-phase commit log records.  It now reports those records properly.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 RT - do not catastrophe on CDS 873 errors (bjo)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed RT to not catastrophe on CDS 873 (CDS_NOT_IN_LUW) errors.  Any application request for rollback will result in a rollback at all the CDServers that the client is connected to.  The application is responsible for taking the proper action when a rollback occurs.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 ODB.dll - Fix DBbegin() to work with the above fix for LUWs. (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Changed DBbegin to work with new cdscl.dll changed in clstubs.c Cds_Rollback().
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 RT.DLL enhancement (cah)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added new entry point into RT.DLL called "async_pcl()" which is a wrapper function around the pcl() routine which saves and restores critical RunTime interpreter state information . Files changed include: \\moa\\src\\rt\\pcl.c, \\moa\\src\\rt\\rt.def.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in displaying debug stuff before connect->ftab was setup.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug of incorrectly returning a value from a no_ret function.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-28-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in parsing and handling hexadecimal (bulk) constants.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b Made v1.4.5 patch #1 to cdsv and cdsodbc here
\par 01-27-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}stop ignoring lengths in comparison of two bulk values.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 1-27-97 moamsg.dll Missing service event log message file (daw)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}The event log message file used by REMSRVR, INITTAB, and other MosaicOA NT services was not included in the distribution.  This only prevented Event Viewer from correctly formatting any error messages logged from these services into the event log, but did not prevent the services from running correctly.  The makefile for moamsg was renamed correctly (was intabmsg.mak) and the dll was added to the distribution (gets installed in system32 directory).
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 1-27-97 RT.DLL Multiple overlapping fields and mouse accessibility (pmm)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}When fields overlap and the mouse is used to select an area that is overlapped by these fields and the first of the overlapping fields in the display list is protected the cursor is not placed within the field. The code was modified to search for the first non-protected in the display list.  Files changed: \\moa\\src\\rt\\mouse.c.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-22-97 mi.exe bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused mi to crash on an assert in _spawnl() when attempting to run udpinfo.exe.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug that caused mi to not find udpinfo.exe when run from a directory where udpinfo.exe did not reside.    [both changes to module network.cpp only]
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-22-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in handling SQLSetPos() with unlock.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added a table to the client-side list of tables during SQLTables() if needed.   So, tables created by others since the ODBC connection was established can be accessed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed a bug in getting the columns of a one-ary table.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug in binding date and time variables with ascii separator characters embedded.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fix bug in SQL "drop index NAME" interpretation.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-22-97 ODB.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in update of CDS record via update current of cursor.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug in DBdropTable() that caused a crash when an identical table was created later.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-21-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in handling order by DESCending in selects.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Added ability to set default dictionary application by name as well as by number.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-20-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in handling next fetch on a cursor after an update that changed the key of the current record for the index used for the cursor.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-17-97 ODB.dll enhancement (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}New function DBgetInfo() an entry to SQLGetInfo().
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-16-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in handling FT_IND, date and time strings as parameters and as literals for where clause criteria.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Again allow psuedo multiple connections to a CDS server from a client, since Access uses them.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-16-97 CDSV package fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Server setup options dialog no longer allows user to enter the CDS directory path.  Whatever they entered on with the previous version was ignored anyway.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}bin_fat\\cdsv.exe and bin_slim|cdsv.exe are deleted on install.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-15-97 ODB.dll bug fixes (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bugs in storing newly created tables in client side array of tables.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed performance problem on inserts that caused too many calls to SQLTables().
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Return -DB_NO_DATA instead of -DB54 from DBgetColumnValue() when prior fetch failed or was never executed.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-15-97 Include directory clean-up (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}deleted x/er.h.  It was duplicated by include\\er.h.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}deleted h/this_sys.h.  It is replaced by include\\this_sys.h.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs24\b 01-15-97 QL.exe (s)
\par \pard\li360\fi-360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Fixed bug inserting from one table to another that cause creation of a context name that was too long.
\par \pard\li360\fi-360\plain\f2\fs20 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs28\cf1\b 
